arch-overlay\" id=\"arxiv-search-overlay\" hidden>\n  <div class=\"arxiv-search-panel\" role=\"search\">\n    <form method=\"GET\" action=\"https://arxiv.org/search\">\n      <label for=\"arxiv-search-input\" class=\"is-sr-only\">Search arXiv</label>\n      <input type=\"text\" name=\"query\" id=\"arxiv-search-input\" autocomplete=\"off\"\n        placeholder=\"Search papers by title, author, abstract, or ID...\">\n      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"searchtype\" value=\"all\">\n      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"source\" value=\"header\">\n    </form>\n    <div class=\"arxiv-search-hint\">\n      Press Enter to search &middot; <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/advanced\">Advanced search</a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n    <main>\n      <div id=\"content\">\n<!--\nrdf:RDF xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\"\n         xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\"\n         xmlns:trackback=\"http://madskills.com/public/xml/rss/module/trackback/\">\n    <rdf:Description\n        rdf:about=\"/abs/2607.06296\"\n        dc:identifier=\"/abs/2607.06296\"\n        dc:title=\"Designing Maintainable Hybrid Generative Systems: A Quantum-Inspired Approach to Automated Music Harmony Generation\"\n        trackback:ping=\"/trackback/2607.06296\" />\n    </rdf:RDF>\n--><div id=\"abs-outer\">\n\n  <div class=\"leftcolumn\">\n    <div class=\"subheader\">\n      <h1>Computer Science > Sound</h1>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"header-breadcrumbs-mobile\">\n      <strong>arXiv:2607.06296v1</strong> (cs)\n    </div>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/static/base/1.0.1/css/abs.css\">\n<div id=\"content-inner\">\n  <div id=\"abs\">\n    <div class=\"dateline\">\n  [Submitted on 7 Jul 2026]</div>\n    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>Designing Maintainable Hybrid Generative Systems: A Quantum-Inspired Approach to Automated Music Harmony Generation</h1>\n    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Pavlicek,+J\" rel=\"nofollow\">Josef Pavlicek</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled Designing Maintainable Hybrid Generative Systems: A Quantum-Inspired Approach to Automated Music Harmony Generation, by Josef Pavlicek</div>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"/pdf/2607.06296v1\">View PDF</a>\n\n\n\n    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>This paper presents the design and evaluation of a maintainable hybrid generative architecture for automated music harmony generation from melody. The proposed system combines quantum-inspired candidate exploration over overlapping melodic contexts with explicit rule-based optimization to balance generative flexibility and structural control. The architecture is evaluated using explicit and reproducible metrics covering structural coherence, functional agreement, harmonic similarity, and robustness. The results show that the proposed approach produces harmonizations that preserve tonal structure and cadential behavior while allowing multiple valid harmonic realizations. Furthermore, the optimization layer improves structural coherence, stability, and predictability without requiring a training corpus. The study demonstrates that transparent and controllable hybrid generative systems can be systematically designed and evaluated within the context of Information Systems Development.\n    </blockquote>\n\n    <!--CONTEXT-->\n    <div class=\"metatable\">\n      <table summary=\"Additional metadata\">        <tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Comments:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell comments mathjax\">12 pages, 1 figure, 4 tables. Extended version of the 4-page paper accepted at the 34th International Conference on Information Systems Development (ISD2026, Prague). Source code and dataset available at <a href=\"https://github.com\" rel=\"external noopener nofollow\" class=\"link-external link-https\">this https URL</a></td>\n        </tr>\n<tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Subjects:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell subjects\">\n            <span class=\"primary-subject\">Sound (cs.SD)</span>; Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI); Emerging Technologies (cs.ET); Audio and Speech Processing (eess.AS)</td>\n        </tr>        <tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\"><abbr title=\"Association of Computing Machinery Classification\">ACM</abbr>&nbsp;classes:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell acm-classes\">I.2.1; I.2.3; D.2.11</td>\n        </tr>\n<tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Cite as:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell arxivid\"><span class=\"arxivid\"><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.06296\">arXiv:2607.06296</a> [cs.SD]</span></td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">&nbsp;</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell arxividv\">(or <span class=\"arxivid\">\n              <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.06296v1\">arXiv:2607.06296v1</a> [cs.SD]</span> for this version)\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">&nbsp;</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell arxivdoi\">              <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2607.06296\"  id=\"arxiv-doi-link\">https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2607.06296</a><div class=\"button-and-tooltip\">\n              <button class=\"more-info\" aria-describedby=\"more-info-desc-1\">\n                <svg height=\"15\" role=\"presentation\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M256 8C119.043 8 8 119.083 8 256c0 136.997 111.043 248 248 248s248-111.003 248-248C504 119.083 392.957 8 256 8zm0 110c23.196 0 42 18.804 42 42s-18.804 42-42 42-42-18.804-42-42 18.804-42 42-42zm56 254c0 6.627-5.373 12-12 12h-88c-6.627 0-12-5.373-12-12v-24c0-6.627 5.373-12 12-12h12v-64h-12c-6.627 0-12-5.373-12-12v-24c0-6.627 5.373-12 12-12h64c6.627 0 12 5.373 12 12v100h12c6.627 0 12 5.373 12 12v24z\" class=\"\"></path></svg>\n                <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Focus to learn more</span>\n              </button>\n              <!-- tooltip description -->\n              <div role=\"tooltip\" id=\"more-info-desc-1\">\n                <span class=\"left-corner\"></span>                  arXiv-issued DOI via DataCite</div>\n            </div>\n          </td>\n        </tr></table>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n    <div class=\"submission-history\">\n      <h2>Submission history</h2> From: Josef Pavlicek Ph.D. [<a href=\"/show-email/7bbe1b2b/2607.06296\" rel=\"nofollow\">view email</a>]      <br/>    <strong>[v1]</strong>\n        Tue, 7 Jul 2026 14:03:10 UTC (3,783 KB)<br/>\n</div>\n  </div>\n  <!--end leftcolumn-->\n<div class=\"extra-services\">    <div class=\"full-text\">\n      <a name=\"other\"></a>\n      <span class=\"descriptor\">Full-text links:</span>\n      <h2>Access Paper:</h2>\n      <ul>\n  <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>\nView a PDF of the paper titled Designing Maintainable Hybrid Generative Systems: A Quantum-Inspired Approach to Automated Music Harmony Generation, by Josef Pavlicek</div><li><a href=\"/pdf/2607.06296v1\" aria-describedby=\"download-button-info\" accesskey=\"f\" class=\"abs-button download-pdf\">View PDF</a></li></ul>\n      <div class=\"abs-license\"><a href=\"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/\" title=\"Rights to this article\">view license</a></div>\n    </div>\n    <!--end full-text-->    <div class=\"browse\">\n    <h3 class=\"browse-context-heading\">Current browse context:</h3>\n  <div class=\"current\">cs.SD</div>\n\n  <div class=\"prevnext\">\n<span class=\"arrow\">\n      <a class=\"abs-button prev-url\" href=\"/prevnext?id=2607.06296&amp;function=prev&amp;context=cs.SD\"\n         accesskey=\"p\" title=\"previous in cs.SD (accesskey p)\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&nbsp;prev</a>\n    </span>